    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 17172/12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Regret no warships could reach Italy before the arrival of the fleet in those
                    waters about January 14, about which we will cable you further. <hi
                        rend="italic">Scorpion</hi> ordered last night from Constantinople. You may
                    possibly find her of use in rendering assistance to American citizens or others
                    in distress or to facilitate communication. Telegram 31st received. May draw for
                    $5,000 if necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
